## 4. The Database (MS SQL Server)

The database is named **`PlacementTrackerDB`** and contains **7 tables**, **3 views**, and **3 stored procedures**.

### 4.1 Tables

#### [Students](file:///c:/Users/Aadithya/OneDrive/Desktop/dbms%20mini/frontend/admin-modules.html#273-300)
Stores login credentials for student accounts.
```
StudentID (PK), FirstName, LastName, RollNumber (UNIQUE), Email (UNIQUE), PasswordHash, CreatedAt
```

#### `StudentProfiles`
Stores academic details. This is kept **separate** from [Students](file:///c:/Users/Aadithya/OneDrive/Desktop/dbms%20mini/frontend/admin-modules.html#273-300) because a student signs up first, then fills their profile later.
```
ProfileID (PK), StudentID (FK → Students), CGPA, Branch, GradYear, Backlogs, UpdatedAt
```
> **Why separate?** If we merged it into Students, every student would need to provide CGPA at signup, which is bad UX. The separation follows the **1NF/2NF normalization principle** — each table has a single responsibility.

#### `Admins`
Stores Placement Officer accounts.
```
AdminID (PK), OperatorName, DepartmentEmail (UNIQUE), PasswordHash, RoleLevel, CreatedAt
```

#### `Companies`
A master table of recruiting companies.
```
CompanyID (PK), Name, LogoInitial, LogoColor, Website, CreatedAt
```

#### [Drives](file:///c:/Users/Aadithya/OneDrive/Desktop/dbms%20mini/frontend/drives.html#168-180)
Each placement drive belongs to one company. Stores role, salary, deadline, and eligibility criteria.
```
DriveID (PK), CompanyID (FK → Companies), Role, PackageLPA, Deadline, Description,
MinCGPA, MaxBacklogs, AllowedBranches, IsActive, CreatedAt
```
> **`FOREIGN KEY REFERENCES Companies(CompanyID)`** — This enforces referential integrity. You cannot create a drive for a company that doesn't exist.

#### [Applications](file:///c:/Users/Aadithya/OneDrive/Desktop/dbms%20mini/frontend/dashboard.html#302-340)
Records which student applied to which drive.
```
ApplicationID (PK), StudentID (FK → Students), DriveID (FK → Drives),
Status (Applied/In Review/Accepted/Rejected), AppliedAt, UpdatedAt
CONSTRAINT UQ_StudentDrive UNIQUE (StudentID, DriveID)  — prevents applying twice
```

#### [Notifications](file:///c:/Users/Aadithya/OneDrive/Desktop/dbms%20mini/frontend/dashboard.html#354-382)
System alerts to students. If `StudentID` is NULL, it is a **broadcast** to everyone.
```
NotificationID (PK), StudentID (FK, nullable), Title, Message, Type, IsRead, CreatedAt
```

#### `Documents`
Stores uploaded transcript/certificate records for verification.
```
DocumentID (PK), StudentID (FK → Students), DocumentType, FileUrl, VerificationStatus, UploadedAt, VerifiedAt
```

