## 5. The Backend API (server.js)

The Node.js server runs on **`http://localhost:3000`** and exposes a REST API. The frontend fetches from this API using JavaScript's `fetch()`.

### Connection Pooling ([db.js](file:///c:/Users/Aadithya/OneDrive/Desktop/dbms%20mini/backend/db.js))
Instead of opening a new database connection on every single request (which would be slow), we create a **connection pool** — a set of pre-opened connections that are reused. `mssql` manages this automatically once `poolPromise` is initialized.

Uses **Windows Authentication** (no username/password needed since both Node and SQL Server run on the same machine under the same Windows account).

### API Routes Summary

| Method | Route | What it does |
|---|---|---|
| `POST` | `/api/auth/student/signup` | Registers a new student (checks for duplicates, hashes password) |
| `POST` | `/api/auth/student/login` | Validates credentials, returns student object to store in localStorage |
| `POST` | `/api/auth/admin/signup` | Registers a new admin |
| `POST` | `/api/auth/admin/login` | Validates admin credentials |
| `GET` | `/api/student/profile?studentId=` | Fetches one student's profile (JOIN query) |
| `POST` | `/api/student/profile` | Creates or updates profile using SQL **MERGE** (upsert) |
| `GET` | `/api/drives` | Returns all active drives via `vw_DriveDetails` |
| `POST` | `/api/drives/:id/apply` | Calls `sp_ApplyToDrive` stored procedure |
| `GET` | `/api/student/eligible-drives` | Calls `sp_GetEligibleDrives` stored procedure |
| `GET` | `/api/student/applications` | Fetches the student's application history from `vw_StudentDashboard` |
