### Parameterized Queries (SQL Injection Prevention)
All queries use `.input('ParamName', sql.Type, value)` — **never** string concatenation. This means even if a malicious user types `'; DROP TABLE Students; --` into a form, it is treated as literal text, not SQL.

```js
// SAFE — parameterized
pool.request().input('Email', sql.NVARCHAR, email).query('SELECT * FROM Students WHERE Email = @Email');

// UNSAFE (we never do this) — vulnerable to SQL injection
pool.request().query(`SELECT * FROM Students WHERE Email = '${email}'`);
```

### Password Hashing
Passwords are passed through `sha256()` before being stored or compared. The hash is a fixed 64-character hex string. Even if someone accessed the database directly, they would see only the hash, not the real password.

