## 7. Key DBMS Concepts Used

| Concept | Where Used |
|---|---|
| **Normalization (1NF, 2NF, 3NF)** | Students and StudentProfiles are separated — no repeating groups |
| **Primary Keys** | Every table has a surrogate `INT IDENTITY` PK |
| **Foreign Keys** | Students←Applications→Drives←Companies — enforces referential integrity |
| **UNIQUE Constraints** | `RollNumber`, `Email` — prevents duplicate registrations |
| **Composite UNIQUE** | `UNIQUE(StudentID, DriveID)` — prevents applying to the same drive twice |
| **Views** | 3 views wrap complex JOINs for reusability |
| **Stored Procedures** | 3 procedures encapsulate business logic (eligibility, application, eligible drives) |
| **MERGE (Upsert)** | Profile creation — INSERT if new, UPDATE if exists |
| **OUTPUT Clause** | Returns the newly inserted ID without a second SELECT |
| **Aggregate Subqueries** | `COUNT(*)` subqueries inside `vw_AdminDashboard` |
| **CHARINDEX()** | String-based branch matching in eligibility checks |
| **Parameterized Queries** | All queries — prevents SQL injection |
| **Conditional Logic in SQL** | IF/ELSE blocks inside stored procedures |
| **Transactions (implicit)** | SQL Server auto-wraps single statements in transactions |

